09:07.434 --> 09:08.696
Wow.

09:08.716 --> 09:14.803
Verse 44, the kingdom of heaven is like treasure hidden in a field.

09:15.604 --> 09:18.988
When a man found it, he hid it again.

09:19.889 --> 09:23.794
And then in his joy went and sold all he had and bought

09:24.354 --> 09:27.559
I have a word from the Lord for you today.

09:27.879 --> 09:30.904
The Lord told me to tell you, it's worth the dirt.

09:33.288 --> 09:35.331
It's worth the dirt.

09:36.933 --> 09:38.856
Father, these moments in your presence are precious.

09:38.917 --> 09:45.967
We pray for your protection and a hedge of your glory around each of your children today so that they can receive what you speak.

09:46.028 --> 09:49.753
However it comes out, this is your word and your church.

09:50.534 --> 09:52.818
In Jesus' name, amen.

09:53.058 --> 09:55.862
Touch your neighbor and tell him it's worth the dirt on your way to your seat.

09:59.067 --> 10:03.152
I know you had to wait for this sermon, but it's going to be worth it.

10:04.875 --> 10:16.351
Now, I have a feeling that this microphone is not going to hold up today, but I think what I'm going to do is I'm just going to preach this as awkward as it needs to be preached unless that becomes so distracting that we can't take it.

10:16.932 --> 10:20.978
And if somebody wants to run the target and buy me a megaphone, I'll preach through that as well.

10:23.202 --> 10:24.503
You know, God is so good.

10:26.265 --> 10:34.152
He teaches us to discern in different seasons of our life whether or not something is worth it.

10:35.454 --> 10:41.119
And maturity is learning to see when something will be worth it and embrace it.

10:42.300 --> 10:46.765
And when it's not worth it to walk away, that's what maturity is.

10:47.205 --> 10:52.530
Being mature in your faith, it's about recognizing when it's worth it,

10:53.314 --> 10:59.541
And when it isn't worth it, and not only recognize it, but walk away when it's not worth it.

10:59.561 --> 11:03.585
Tell your neighbor, just practice real quick, say, it's not even worth it.

11:05.387 --> 11:06.348
It's not even worth it.

11:07.169 --> 11:10.133
Some things are, some things aren't.

11:10.153 --> 11:15.659
For years, when I would go watch Graham Wrestle, usually I would spend my Saturdays in a sweaty gym that smelled like boy.

11:17.060 --> 11:18.622
Smelled like the worst parts of a boy.

11:19.203 --> 11:22.226
By about two o'clock in the afternoon, it would be cooking in that oven.

11:22.562 --> 11:32.214
The reason I know that it was worth it is because the first time he ever won a big wrestling tournament, I said to him afterwards, man, I'm so glad I was here to see it.

11:32.294 --> 11:40.324
Now, the reason that I almost wasn't there was because I had to bring in a guest preacher to preach for me in order to be at his tournament.

11:40.624 --> 11:47.372
And there was a part of me sitting there like, man, thousands of people that need the gospel and then my son's wrestling, I don't know what to do.

11:47.412 --> 11:49.996
Is it worth it to not preach to go watch him in this tournament?

11:50.396 --> 11:52.018
So he wins the whole thing, right?

11:52.450 --> 12:01.066
and we're sitting at Pizza Hut, where all of my food addiction issues began with the Booket Club.

12:03.992 --> 12:13.650
I'm serious, all of my food reward issues started in the fourth grade, reading the babysitter's club, and getting pizza for it shouldn't have confessed that.

12:15.138 --> 12:19.923
Well, we're sitting there at Pizza Hut celebrating his gold medal, and I said, man, I'm so glad I came.

12:20.203 --> 12:22.446
What if you'd have won the whole tournament and I hadn't been here to see it?

12:22.526 --> 12:26.210
And he said, well, if you hadn't been here to see it, I probably wouldn't have won it.

12:29.053 --> 12:31.716
If you hadn't been here to see it, I probably wouldn't have won it.

12:33.738 --> 12:42.928
So every time I'd be hauling my butt into a gym with some boys' feet propped up on the bleachers behind me, I mean, at a wrestling tournament, they turned the whole gym into a locker room.

12:42.968 --> 12:44.229
It's awesome.

12:44.249 --> 12:45.010
It's incredible.

12:46.146 --> 12:52.534
and in a room full of half-naked men packed to the gills, and me sitting there in the middle of all of it with my OCD.

12:53.115 --> 12:55.518
I'm going, it's worth it, it's worth it, it's worth it, it's worth it, it's worth it.

12:55.958 --> 12:59.503
Not just because he's going to go to the Olympics, but because he told me it's worth it.

13:00.704 --> 13:04.469
Tell somebody, sometimes it's worth it.

13:04.489 --> 13:08.274
Sometimes you got to preach with the mic popping because it's worth it.

13:09.315 --> 13:14.642
Sometimes you got to come out to church a day early on a Saturday because it's worth it.

13:16.226 --> 13:17.247
Sometimes it's worth it.

13:18.609 --> 13:20.852
And wisdom is knowing when it's worth it.

13:22.395 --> 13:28.403
Wisdom is the ability to hear that little whisper that God will give you from time to time and say, it's worth it.

13:28.423 --> 13:31.447
Stick with this, it's worth it.

13:31.467 --> 13:32.969
Log on church online today.

13:33.390 --> 13:34.211
It's gonna be worth it.

13:35.974 --> 13:37.796
Yeah, keep trying to fix that relationship.

13:38.437 --> 13:39.278
It's worth it.

13:39.298 --> 13:40.680
And sometimes it's just a little whisper.

13:40.960 --> 13:44.946
God will encourage you in the moment where you feel like giving up and he'll say, no, no, no, it's worth it.

13:45.602 --> 13:47.124
keep doing it, it's worth it.

13:48.186 --> 13:50.148
Just whisper to your neighbor, say, it's worth it.

13:51.490 --> 13:53.453
Not something to say, it's worth it when it's worth it.

13:55.516 --> 14:06.291
But you know what, I had a moment the other day, and it happened when I was bending down the time I choose, and Holly was in the other room laughing at me, and she said, babe, your time, your shoe's like you are 88.

14:07.854 --> 14:10.698
And I said, I know, babe, I can't help it.

14:10.718 --> 14:13.842
That's the price that I pay for this physique.

14:16.066 --> 14:17.528
It just comes with soreness.

14:18.871 --> 14:27.986
And she said, yeah, but the trade-off, like you look great, but do you really have to go that hard on leg day that you can't tie your shoes?

14:28.627 --> 14:32.754
And I had a moment standing there in the closet, listening to my wife mock me.

14:34.498 --> 14:36.681
a moment of maturity where I decided, you know what?

14:36.701 --> 14:37.102
She's right.

14:37.122 --> 14:38.144
This is not worth it.

14:38.684 --> 14:46.456
Even though that lady at the gym 15 years ago made fun of me and said, do you ever do leg day and created a complex inside of me while I was wearing my shorts?

14:46.937 --> 14:51.003
I was bending down to tie my shoes and something just hit me real quick like, you know what?

14:51.985 --> 14:52.786
Nobody.

14:53.026 --> 14:54.630
is looking at your hamstrings.

14:55.512 --> 14:58.420
Nobody, not even Holly wants to see your hamstrings.

14:58.901 --> 15:02.290
So just wear some sweats and cover your quads.

15:02.310 --> 15:04.115
What are you trying to be, a quad model?

15:04.395 --> 15:10.130
And that was the last day I ever did heavy squats, because it's not worth it.

15:10.722 --> 15:13.386
I came to set somebody free from leg day today.

15:13.787 --> 15:15.309
You're too old for that now.

15:15.689 --> 15:17.933
You're not supposed to be going down that deep.

15:18.353 --> 15:22.620
If the Lord would have made you to bend down like that, He'd have put hinges on your hips.

15:23.140 --> 15:26.806
It's not helping anybody and nobody is looking at your calves.

15:27.166 --> 15:28.268
Cover them up.

15:28.288 --> 15:30.111
It's not worth it.

15:31.172 --> 15:32.454
Wear some baggy jeans.

15:33.135 --> 15:34.678
Tie your shoes and be happy.

15:38.864 --> 15:40.306
In Matthew chapter 13,

15:41.890 --> 15:42.711
What a transition.

15:44.153 --> 15:46.556
Pulling out all the stops today on Snow Day.

15:46.576 --> 15:55.228
In Matthew chapter 13, Jesus is giving a very important lesson to his disciples on what's worth it.

15:57.051 --> 16:03.660
Because he knows there will be a time soon to come when he goes to the cross and their commitment to him will be challenged by that cross.

16:04.641 --> 16:06.143
See, they left a lot to follow him.

16:06.965 --> 16:08.266
They left their fishing businesses.

16:08.306 --> 16:10.930
They left their tax collecting agencies.

16:11.522 --> 16:21.873
Many of them even left their family's approval to follow this wonder-working rebel priest named Jesus of Nazareth, who was considered a heretic by many.

16:22.774 --> 16:29.721
And at the moment that he could have called the Legion of Angels to get him down off the cross and did, and I wondered, did they wonder, was it worth it?

16:31.663 --> 16:35.647
And I wonder who I'm preaching to today that wonders, is it worth it?

16:37.669 --> 16:38.450
Is it worth it?

16:38.882 --> 16:41.485
For me to keep serving God, it doesn't seem to be doing me any good.

16:41.525 --> 16:45.950
Is it worth it for me to keep being pure as a teenager?

16:45.990 --> 16:47.752
Everybody else is having more fun than I am.

16:49.174 --> 16:57.303
Is it worth it for me to be the weird kid that doesn't get invited to the parties because I have a standard of purity and I have a direction of destiny?

16:59.165 --> 17:06.994
I have learned at this stage of my life how important it is that we are not driven by external and

17:07.650 --> 17:11.375
Others focused metrics of what matters.

17:12.557 --> 17:15.320
You have to decide what is worth it from within.

17:16.622 --> 17:17.183
You have to.

17:18.064 --> 17:19.506
Or else you'll jump on every trend.

17:20.928 --> 17:24.873
Or else you will burn yourself out and then ask God to light your fire.

17:24.953 --> 17:34.126
But God can't light a fire when you don't have the priorities to put His presence first in your life.

17:35.508 --> 17:37.330
And I think this is your year to decide.

17:37.890 --> 17:43.836
what's worth it to you and to commit to what is and to walk away from what isn't.

17:45.297 --> 17:46.778
This is not permission to quit your job.

17:48.941 --> 17:50.022
Because I bet you like that check.

17:50.042 --> 17:51.083
That check is kind of worth it.

17:52.544 --> 17:53.225
It's kind of worth it.

17:53.245 --> 17:55.246
It's kind of worth your boss's bad breath, isn't it?

17:56.047 --> 17:57.609
The health insurance is kind of worth it.

17:57.629 --> 18:00.672
That dental insurance make you put up with a lot of stuff.

18:02.153 --> 18:05.196
See, I think it's very difficult for us in the moment to know, is it worth it?

18:05.216 --> 18:07.378
It's easy to look back and say that wasn't worth it.

18:08.322 --> 18:09.984
It's easy to look back and say that was worth it.

18:11.185 --> 18:18.112
Where the Holy Spirit comes in is to look at something and to realize this is worth it and the Lord will whisper, it's worth it.

18:18.132 --> 18:20.835
I know it doesn't look like much, but it's worth it.

18:21.175 --> 18:24.759
I know it's hard for you and nobody's appreciating you, but it's worth it.

18:24.779 --> 18:25.820
I've called you to it.

18:25.840 --> 18:29.364
And then the Holy Spirit will whisper to you sometimes, it's not worth it.

18:29.804 --> 18:31.205
I know you want to tell them off.

18:34.188 --> 18:35.730
Save your breath, it's not worth it.

18:36.898 --> 18:43.689
I know you want to put them in their place and you can do it, but it's not worth it.

18:43.709 --> 18:46.854
You're going to be sore tomorrow if you go off today.

18:47.215 --> 18:51.301
Now you're going to have to apologize and create more work for yourself.

18:52.143 --> 18:53.124
Just put it in the comments.

18:53.164 --> 18:53.885
It's not worth it.

18:55.308 --> 18:58.353
I learned that about leg day, but I'm still learning it about life.

19:00.336 --> 19:04.242
I'm learning that it is not worth it for me to respond to every criticism.

19:05.026 --> 19:07.769
I mean, let's be honest, I've had my fair share of practice.

19:08.569 --> 19:11.812
How many of y'all that go to this church have ever heard somebody say something bad about me?

19:13.314 --> 19:15.696
How many of you wanted to punch them in the mouth?

19:15.716 --> 19:17.317
I love y'all.

19:17.338 --> 19:18.839
That's our real church right there.

19:20.400 --> 19:25.445
One of my friends asked me one time, he's like, pastor, don't you feel like the staff you got around you is too saved?

19:25.886 --> 19:32.091
Don't you feel like you need a few barely saved just out of prison ministry staff around you just to handle the nonsense?

19:32.151 --> 19:34.994
I thought, no, it's not worth it.

19:35.842 --> 19:36.764
Peter didn't get this.

19:36.804 --> 19:41.532
When they came to get Jesus, he started cutting off ears and Jesus said, what is this?

19:42.433 --> 19:44.857
It's not worth it.

19:45.699 --> 19:49.205
Nothing can stop me from going to the cross because that's what God sent me to do.

19:49.605 --> 19:51.749
It's not worth it.

19:53.392 --> 19:54.894
That phrase right there will set you free.

19:55.155 --> 19:55.836
It's not worth it.

19:56.818 --> 19:58.380
It's not worth it.

19:58.400 --> 20:01.746
Because if I defend myself to a critic and I win, what have I won?

20:06.882 --> 20:08.485
a critic who changed their mind?

20:09.107 --> 20:11.191
What prize do I get for changing their mind?

20:12.694 --> 20:14.217
If I change your mind, I get what?

20:14.498 --> 20:19.970
See, I might win an argument, but it's too expensive because it cost me my peace.

20:22.515 --> 20:25.842
So I'd rather keep my peace than win an argument.

20:27.330 --> 20:30.374
Jesus is helping his disciples to discern what's worth it.

20:30.635 --> 20:32.337
And that's what he's doing in your life right now.

20:32.617 --> 20:34.320
He's allowing some things to be pruned.

20:34.700 --> 20:36.422
He's allowing some things to be moved.

20:36.723 --> 20:39.987
He's allowing some people that were in your life to move to a different circle.

20:40.047 --> 20:41.329
It's not that you don't love them.

20:41.389 --> 20:45.194
It's just that you can't invest in everybody in this season of your life.

20:45.695 --> 20:53.746
And so God graciously moves people into different seasons so that you can focus on what's right in front of you so God can show you what's

20:53.986 --> 20:54.667
worth it.

20:55.067 --> 20:59.953
That's why God let you have that really bad hangover so you could realize this is not worth it.

21:00.273 --> 21:02.556
I don't want to pass this crap on to my kids.

21:02.976 --> 21:07.521
I don't want them to have to struggle with this addiction because it's not worth it.

21:09.163 --> 21:16.431
And in Matthew chapter 13, we get two parables of seven that are mentioned by Jesus in the gospel of Matthew.

21:16.812 --> 21:18.454
They are the mysteries of the kingdom.

21:19.094 --> 21:22.418
One of those mysteries is the mystery of the mustard seed.

21:22.690 --> 21:24.933
And one is the treasure in the field.

21:25.034 --> 21:28.539
And what they both hold in common to me is not apparent on the surface.

21:29.100 --> 21:35.850
He told them another parable, the kingdom of heaven is like a mustard seed, which a man took and planted in his field.

21:36.511 --> 21:43.922
That's a beautiful scripture to me because a mustard seed is indeed the parabolic smallest seed that was known at the time.

